CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 29, 1952, pg. 16, reads: "Attend Capital Seminar - Wilkie Johnson and Arthur Charles review notes after attending the seminar for teenagers sponsored by the American Friends Service Committee in Washington, D. C. last week-end. The Emanons Co-ed Club sent these these two delegates to meet other teen-agers throughout the Mid-Atlantic Region to discuss America's foreign policy.  This club is a part of the Teen-Age Department of the Centre Avenue Branch YWCA. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Wilkie Johnson and Arthur Charles standing behind table with religious books, possibly in Centre Avenue branch of YWCA
